9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
10 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 353.31 of Title 59, unless there
12 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. In accordance with a standing order issued by a licensed
14 allopathic or osteopathic physician or by the medical director of a
15 county or local health department, a pharmacist may test or screen
16 for and initiate drug therapy for minor, nonchronic health
17 conditions as defined in Section 353.1 of Title 59 of the Oklahoma
18 Statutes.
19 B. To test for minor, nonchronic health conditions under this
20 section, the pharmacist may use any test that may guide clinical
21 decision-making and that is:
22 1. Approved by, cleared by, or authorized under an emergency
23 use authorization by the United States Food and Drug Administration;
24 and
