1 2. Waived under the federal Clinical Laboratory Improvement
2 Amendments of 1988 (CLIA) or deemed to be CLIA-waived for use in
3 patient care settings operating under a CLIA certificate.
4 C. A pharmacist shall not test or screen for streptococcus or
5 initiate drug therapy for streptococcus to individuals under six (6)
6 years of age.
